### System information

- **OS version/distro**:  Windows 10 Home
- **.NET Version (eg., dotnet --info)**:  .net core 2.2.0

### Issue
I updated Nuget package from ML 0.8 to 0.11. I have a truble. 
My csv File contain:

SECID,CurrentDate,OpenPrice,FareClosePrice
LKOH,2019-01-01,4984.00,5007.00



### Source code / logs

  _textLoader = mlContext.Data.CreateTextLoader(
                separatorChar: ',',
                hasHeader: true,
                columns: new TextLoader.Column[]
                {
                    new TextLoader.Column("SECID", DataKind.String, 0),
                    new TextLoader.Column("CurrentDate", DataKind.DateTime, 1),
                    new TextLoader.Column("OpenPrice", DataKind.Double, 2),
                    new TextLoader.Column("FareClosePrice", DataKind.Double, 3)
                });

           IDataView dataView = _textLoader.Load(dataPath);
            var pipeline = mlContext.Transforms.CopyColumns("Label", "FareClosePrice")
                .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Categorical.OneHotEncoding("SECID"))
                .Append(mlContext.Transforms.Concatenate("Features", "SECID", "CurrentDate", "OpenPrice", "FareClosePrice"))
            .Append(mlContext.Regression.Trainers.FastTree());

// An error occurs here:  System.InvalidOperationException: "Column 'CurrentDate' has values of // DateTimewhich is not the same as earlier observed type of R4."

            var model = pipeline.Fit(dataView);

It is possible to fit an ONNX model by itself:

```cs
var onnxEstimator = mlContext.Transforms.ApplyOnnxModel(modelPath)
var onnxModel = onnxEstimator.Fit(data);
```

But it throws when it is part of a pipeline:
```cs
var onnxEstimator = mlContext.Transforms.ApplyOnnxModel(modelPath)
    // TODO #2980: ONNX outputs don't match the outputs of the model, so we must hand-correct this for now.
    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.CopyColumns("Score", "Score0"));
    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.CopyColumns("Label", "Fable"));
    .Append(mlContext.Transforms.NormalizeLpNorm("Features2", "Features", LpNormNormalizingEstimatorBase.NormFunction.L2));
var onnxModel = onnxEstimator.Fit(data);
```
Any of these `Append` statements cause a throw. They do not affect the ONNX model at all, and use either the result of the calculation (`Score0`), rows unused by the model (`Label`) or rows also used by the transform (`Features`).

In this case, the error message is:
`System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException : Schema mismatch for input column 'Label': expected vector, got R4
Parameter name: inputSchema`
